description:
Laura Ingraham Podcast June 1 , 2016Wednesday, June 01, 2016

BABIN: Criminal Aliens Granted A 'Revolving Back Door' Onto Our Streets 


Guest Lineup
David Drucker - Senior Congressional Correspondent
Rep. Brian Babin (R-TX)

How the Senate Is Supposed to Work
Mitch McConnell - The Wall Street Journal
People often ask me what President Obama is like. I always tell them the same thing. He's pleasant enough, but he's also like the kid in class who exerts a lot of energy trying to make sure everybody thinks he's the smartest guy in the room. He is also a very liberal guy who is determined to force our country into the kind of progressive model that Western European societies embraced years ago, whether the rest of us like it or not.

BABIN: Criminal Aliens Granted a 'Revolving Back Door' onto our Streets
On today's program, Rep. Brian Babin (R-TX) discussed his new bill, the Criminal Alien Deportation Act. This legislation is designed to "start twisting the arms" of foreign nations that refuse to accept criminal aliens back into their countries. Babin's bill proposes cutting off foreign aid to nations that refuse to cooperate, and immediately cutting off their visa program until they comply.

Shirley Husar - Columnist writer for the Washington Times; CA Delegate

How Clinton can own her email scandal
Charles D. Elliso - The Hill
Somehow, somewhere along the campaigning way, badly placed emails became a political "thing."


Clinton Might Not Be the Nominee
Douglas E. Schoen - The Wall Street Journal
There is now more than a theoretical chance that Hillary Clinton may not be the Democratic nominee for president.
